  "root_text": {
    "snp4.14:0.1": "Sutta Nipāta 4.14 ",
    "snp4.14:0.2": "Tuvaṭakasutta ",
    "snp4.14:1.1": "“Pucchāmi taṁ ādiccabandhu, ",
    "snp4.14:1.2": "Vivekaṁ santipadañca mahesi; ",
    "snp4.14:1.3": "Kathaṁ disvā nibbāti bhikkhu, ",
    "snp4.14:1.4": "Anupādiyāno lokasmiṁ kiñci”. ",
    "snp4.14:2.1": "“Mūlaṁ papañcasaṅkhāya, ",
    "snp4.14:2.2": "(iti bhagavā) ",
    "snp4.14:2.3": "Mantā asmīti sabbamuparundhe; ",
    "snp4.14:2.4": "Yā kāci taṇhā ajjhattaṁ, ",
    "snp4.14:2.5": "Tāsaṁ vinayā sadā sato sikkhe. ",
    "snp4.14:3.1": "Yaṁ kiñci dhammamabhijaññā, ",
    "snp4.14:3.2": "Ajjhattaṁ atha vāpi bahiddhā; ",
    "snp4.14:3.3": "Na tena thāmaṁ kubbetha, ",
    "snp4.14:3.4": "Na hi sā nibbuti sataṁ vuttā. ",
    "snp4.14:4.1": "Seyyo na tena maññeyya, ",
    "snp4.14:4.2": "Nīceyyo atha vāpi sarikkho; ",
    "snp4.14:4.3": "Phuṭṭho anekarūpehi, ",
    "snp4.14:4.4": "Nātumānaṁ vikappayaṁ tiṭṭhe. ",
    "snp4.14:5.1": "Ajjhattamevupasame, ",
    "snp4.14:5.2": "Na aññato bhikkhu santimeseyya; ",
    "snp4.14:5.3": "Ajjhattaṁ upasantassa, ",
    "snp4.14:5.4": "Natthi attā kuto nirattā vā. ",
    "snp4.14:6.1": "Majjhe yathā samuddassa, ",
    "snp4.14:6.2": "Ūmi no jāyatī ṭhito hoti; ",
    "snp4.14:6.3": "Evaṁ ṭhito anejassa, ",
    "snp4.14:6.4": "Ussadaṁ bhikkhu na kareyya kuhiñci”. ",
    "snp4.14:7.1": "“Akittayī vivaṭacakkhu, ",
    "snp4.14:7.2": "Sakkhidhammaṁ parissayavinayaṁ; ",
    "snp4.14:7.3": "Paṭipadaṁ vadehi bhaddante, ",
    "snp4.14:7.4": "Pātimokkhaṁ atha vāpi samādhiṁ”. ",
    "snp4.14:8.1": "“Cakkhūhi neva lolassa, ",
    "snp4.14:8.2": "Gāmakathāya āvaraye sotaṁ; ",
    "snp4.14:8.3": "Rase ca nānugijjheyya, ",
    "snp4.14:8.4": "Na ca mamāyetha kiñci lokasmiṁ. ",
    "snp4.14:9.1": "Phassena yadā phuṭṭhassa, ",
    "snp4.14:9.2": "Paridevaṁ bhikkhu na kareyya kuhiñci; ",
    "snp4.14:9.3": "Bhavañca nābhijappeyya, ",
    "snp4.14:9.4": "Bheravesu ca na sampavedheyya. ",
    "snp4.14:10.1": "Annānamatho pānānaṁ, ",
    "snp4.14:10.2": "Khādanīyānaṁ athopi vatthānaṁ; ",
    "snp4.14:10.3": "Laddhā na sannidhiṁ kayirā, ",
    "snp4.14:10.4": "Na ca parittase tāni alabhamāno. ",
    "snp4.14:11.1": "Jhāyī na pādalolassa, ",
    "snp4.14:11.2": "Virame kukkuccā nappamajjeyya; ",
    "snp4.14:11.3": "Athāsanesu sayanesu, ",
    "snp4.14:11.4": "Appasaddesu bhikkhu vihareyya. ",
    "snp4.14:12.1": "Niddaṁ na bahulīkareyya, ",
    "snp4.14:12.2": "Jāgariyaṁ bhajeyya ātāpī; ",
    "snp4.14:12.3": "Tandiṁ māyaṁ hassaṁ khiḍḍaṁ, ",
    "snp4.14:12.4": "Methunaṁ vippajahe savibhūsaṁ. ",
    "snp4.14:13.1": "Āthabbaṇaṁ supinaṁ lakkhaṇaṁ, ",
    "snp4.14:13.2": "No vidahe athopi nakkhattaṁ; ",
    "snp4.14:13.3": "Virutañca gabbhakaraṇaṁ, ",
    "snp4.14:13.4": "Tikicchaṁ māmako na seveyya. ",
    "snp4.14:14.1": "Nindāya nappavedheyya, ",
    "snp4.14:14.2": "Na uṇṇameyya pasaṁsito bhikkhu; ",
    "snp4.14:14.3": "Lobhaṁ saha macchariyena, ",
    "snp4.14:14.4": "Kodhaṁ pesuṇiyañca panudeyya. ",
    "snp4.14:15.1": "Kayavikkaye na tiṭṭheyya, ",
    "snp4.14:15.2": "Upavādaṁ bhikkhu na kareyya kuhiñci; ",
    "snp4.14:15.3": "Gāme ca nābhisajjeyya, ",
    "snp4.14:15.4": "Lābhakamyā janaṁ na lapayeyya. ",
    "snp4.14:16.1": "Na ca katthitā siyā bhikkhu, ",
    "snp4.14:16.2": "Na ca vācaṁ payuttaṁ bhāseyya; ",
    "snp4.14:16.3": "Pāgabbhiyaṁ na sikkheyya, ",
    "snp4.14:16.4": "Kathaṁ viggāhikaṁ na kathayeyya. ",
    "snp4.14:17.1": "Mosavajje na nīyetha, ",
    "snp4.14:17.2": "Sampajāno saṭhāni na kayirā; ",
    "snp4.14:17.3": "Atha jīvitena paññāya, ",
    "snp4.14:17.4": "Sīlabbatena nāññamatimaññe. ",
    "snp4.14:18.1": "Sutvā rusito bahuṁ vācaṁ, ",
    "snp4.14:18.2": "Samaṇānaṁ vā puthujanānaṁ; ",
    "snp4.14:18.3": "Pharusena ne na paṭivajjā, ",
    "snp4.14:18.4": "Na hi santo paṭisenikaronti. ",
    "snp4.14:19.1": "Etañca dhammamaññāya, ",
    "snp4.14:19.2": "Vicinaṁ bhikkhu sadā sato sikkhe; ",
    "snp4.14:19.3": "Santīti nibbutiṁ ñatvā, ",
    "snp4.14:19.4": "Sāsane gotamassa na pamajjeyya. ",
    "snp4.14:20.1": "Abhibhū hi so anabhibhūto, ",
    "snp4.14:20.2": "Sakkhidhammamanītihamadassī; ",
    "snp4.14:20.3": "Tasmā hi tassa bhagavato sāsane, ",
    "snp4.14:20.4": "Appamatto sadā namassamanusikkhe”ti. ",
    "snp4.14:20.5": "Tuvaṭakasuttaṁ cuddasamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "snp4.14:0.1": "Anthology of Discourses 4.14 ",
    "snp4.14:0.2": "Speedy ",
    "snp4.14:1.1": "“Great seer, I ask you, the Kinsman of the Sun, ",
    "snp4.14:1.2": "about seclusion and the state of peace. ",
    "snp4.14:1.3": "How, having seen, is a mendicant extinguished, ",
    "snp4.14:1.4": "not grasping anything in this world?” ",
    "snp4.14:2.1": "“They would cut off the idea, ‘I am the thinker,” ",
    "snp4.14:2.2": "said the Buddha, ",
    "snp4.14:2.3": "“which is the root of all judgments <j>that emerge from proliferation. ",
    "snp4.14:2.4": "Ever mindful, they would train to remove ",
    "snp4.14:2.5": "any internal cravings. ",
    "snp4.14:3.1": "Regardless of what things they know, ",
    "snp4.14:3.2": "whether internal or external, ",
    "snp4.14:3.3": "they wouldn’t be proud because of that, ",
    "snp4.14:3.4": "for that is not quenching, say the good. ",
    "snp4.14:4.1": "They wouldn’t let that make them conceited, ",
    "snp4.14:4.2": "thinking themselves better or worse or alike. ",
    "snp4.14:4.3": "When questioned in many ways, ",
    "snp4.14:4.4": "they wouldn’t keep justifying themselves. ",
    "snp4.14:5.1": "A mendicant would find peace inside themselves, ",
    "snp4.14:5.2": "and not seek peace from another. ",
    "snp4.14:5.3": "For one at peace inside themselves, ",
    "snp4.14:5.4": "there’s no picking up, whence putting down? ",
    "snp4.14:6.1": "Just as, in the middle of the ocean, ",
    "snp4.14:6.2": "no waves arise, it stays still; ",
    "snp4.14:6.3": "so too one unstirred is still—",
    "snp4.14:6.4": "a mendicant would make <j>no pretension regarding anything.” ",
    "snp4.14:7.1": "“He whose eyes are open has explained ",
    "snp4.14:7.2": "the truth he witnessed, <j>where adversities are removed. ",
    "snp4.14:7.3": "Please now speak of the practice, sir, ",
    "snp4.14:7.4": "the monastic code and immersion in samādhi.” ",
    "snp4.14:8.1": "“With eyes not wanton, ",
    "snp4.14:8.2": "they’d turn their ears from village gossip. ",
    "snp4.14:8.3": "They wouldn’t be greedy for flavors, ",
    "snp4.14:8.4": "nor possessive about anything in the world. ",
    "snp4.14:9.1": "Though struck by contacts, ",
    "snp4.14:9.2": "a mendicant would not lament at all. ",
    "snp4.14:9.3": "They wouldn’t pray for another life, ",
    "snp4.14:9.4": "nor tremble in the face of dangers. ",
    "snp4.14:10.1": "When they receive food and drink, ",
    "snp4.14:10.2": "edibles and clothes, ",
    "snp4.14:10.3": "they wouldn’t store them up, ",
    "snp4.14:10.4": "nor worry about not getting them. ",
    "snp4.14:11.1": "Meditative, not footloose, ",
    "snp4.14:11.2": "they’d avoid remorse and not be negligent. ",
    "snp4.14:11.3": "Then a mendicant would stay ",
    "snp4.14:11.4": "in quiet places to sit and rest. ",
    "snp4.14:12.1": "They wouldn’t take much sleep, ",
    "snp4.14:12.2": "but, being keen, <j>would apply themselves to wakefulness. ",
    "snp4.14:12.3": "They’d give up sloth, illusion, mirth, and play, ",
    "snp4.14:12.4": "and sex and ornamentation. ",
    "snp4.14:13.1": "They wouldn’t cast Artharvaṇa spells, <j>interpret dreams ",
    "snp4.14:13.2": "or omens, or practice astrology. ",
    "snp4.14:13.3": "My followers would not study ominous animal cries, ",
    "snp4.14:13.4": "work as a doctor, or treat an impacted fetus. ",
    "snp4.14:14.1": "Not shaken by criticism, ",
    "snp4.14:14.2": "a mendicant would not gloat when praised. ",
    "snp4.14:14.3": "They’d cast aside greed and stinginess, ",
    "snp4.14:14.4": "anger, and slander. ",
    "snp4.14:15.1": "They’d not stand for buying and selling; ",
    "snp4.14:15.2": "a mendicant would not speak ill at all. ",
    "snp4.14:15.3": "They wouldn’t linger in the village, ",
    "snp4.14:15.4": "nor cajole people from desire for profit. ",
    "snp4.14:16.1": "A mendicant would be no boaster, ",
    "snp4.14:16.2": "nor would they speak suggestively. ",
    "snp4.14:16.3": "They wouldn’t train in impudence, ",
    "snp4.14:16.4": "nor speak argumentatively. ",
    "snp4.14:17.1": "They wouldn’t be led into lying, ",
    "snp4.14:17.2": "nor be deliberately devious. ",
    "snp4.14:17.3": "And they’d never look down on another ",
    "snp4.14:17.4": "because of livelihood, wisdom, or precepts and vows. ",
    "snp4.14:18.1": "Though provoked from hearing much talk ",
    "snp4.14:18.2": "from ascetics saying all different things, ",
    "snp4.14:18.3": "they wouldn’t react harshly, ",
    "snp4.14:18.4": "for the virtuous do not retaliate. ",
    "snp4.14:19.1": "Having understood this teaching, ",
    "snp4.14:19.2": "inquiring, a mendicant would always train mindfully. ",
    "snp4.14:19.3": "Knowing quenching as peace, ",
    "snp4.14:19.4": "they’d not be negligent in Gotama’s bidding. ",
    "snp4.14:20.1": "For he is the vanquisher, the unvanquished, ",
    "snp4.14:20.2": "seer of the truth as witness, not by hearsay—",
    "snp4.14:20.3": "that’s why, being diligent, they would always train ",
    "snp4.14:20.4": "respectfully in the Buddha’s teaching.” "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "snp4.14:1.1": "ādiccabandhu → ādiccabandhuṁ (bj, sya-all, pts-vp-pli1) ",
    "snp4.14:2.3": "sabbamuparundhe → sabbamuparuddhe (sya-all, mr) ",
    "snp4.14:2.5": "vinayā → vinayāya (?) ",
    "snp4.14:3.3": "thāmaṁ → mānaṁ (bj, mr) ",
    "snp4.14:4.3": "Phuṭṭho → puṭṭho (sya-all, pts-vp-pli1, mr) ",
    "snp4.14:10.2": "Khādanīyānaṁ athopi → khādanīyānamathopi (mnd14:119 [Tuvaṭakasuttaniddesa]) ",
    "snp4.14:17.1": "nīyetha → niyyetha (bj, sya-all mnd14:201 [Tuvaṭakasuttaniddesa]) ",
    "snp4.14:18.2": "Samaṇānaṁ vā puthujanānaṁ → samaṇānaṁ puthuvacanānaṁ (bj, sya-all, pts-vp-pli1) ",
    "snp4.14:19.4": "na pamajjeyya → nappamajjeyya (bj, sya-all mnd14:214 [Tuvaṭakasuttaniddesa]) "
  },
